M||desc|>-
M||tx|When the us wants to plan, ds, or im an A/B tst or experiment, or bd a growth experimentation program. Also use when the us mentions "A/B tst," "split tst," "experiment," "tst this change," "variant cp," "multivariate tst," "hypothesis," "shd I tst this," "which version is better," "tst two versions," "statistical significance," "how long shd I run this tst," "growth experiments," "experiment velocity," "experiment backlog," "ICE score," "experimentation program," or "experiment playbook." Use this whenever someone is comparing two approaches and wants to measure which performs better, or when they want to bd a systematic experimentation practice. For tracking implementation, see an-tracking. For page-level conversion op, see page-cro.
