M|The |tx|Looking at results before reaching sample size and stopping early leads to false positives and wrong decisions. Pre-commit to sample size and trust the process.
M|The |tx|---
M|Stat|it|95% confidence = p-value < 0.05
M|Stat|it|Means <5% chance result is random
M|Stat|it|Not a guarantee—just a threshold
M|Anal|tx|1. **Reach sample size?** If not, result is preliminary
M|Anal|tx|2. **Statistically sig?** Check confidence intervals
M|Anal|tx|3. **Effect size meaningful?** Compare to MDE, project impact
M|Anal|tx|4. **Secondary metrics consistent?** Support the primary?
M|Anal|tx|5. **Guardrail concerns?** Anything get worse?
M|Anal|tx|6. **Segment differences?** Mobile vs. desktop? New vs. returning?
M|Inte|tx|\| Result \| Conclusion \|
M|Inte|tx|\|--------\|------------\|
M|Inte|tx|\| sig winner \| im variant \|
M|Inte|tx|\| sig loser \| Keep control, learn why \|
M|Inte|tx|\| No sig difference \| Need more traffic or bolder tst \|
M|Inte|tx|\| Mixed signals \| Dig deeper, maybe segment \|
