M|doc|tx|---
M|Grow|tx|Individual tests are valuable. A continuous experimentation program is a compounding asset. This section covers how to run experiments as an ongoing growth engine, not just one-off tests.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|1. gn hypotheses (from data, research, cr, cs feedback)
M|The |tx|2. Prioritize w/ ICE scoring
M|The |tx|3. ds and run the tst
M|The |tx|4. al results w/ statistical rigor
M|The |tx|5. Promote winners to a playbook
M|The |tx|6. gn new hypotheses from learnings
M|The |tx|→ Repeat
M|The |tx|```
M|Hypo|Feed|
M|Hypo|tx|\| Source \| What to Look For \|
M|Hypo|tx|\|--------\|-----------------\|
M|Hypo|tx|\| an \| Drop-off points, lo-converting pages, underperforming segments \|
M|Hypo|tx|\| cs research \| Pain points, confusion, unmet expectations \|
M|Hypo|tx|\| cr al \| Features, messaging, or UX patterns they use that you don't \|
M|Hypo|tx|\| Support tickets \| Recurring questions or complaints abt conversion flows \|
M|Hypo|tx|\| Heatmaps/recordings \| Where us hesitate, rage-click, or abandon \|
M|Hypo|tx|\| Past experiments \| "sig loser" tests often reveal new angles to try \|
M|ICE |Scor|
M|ICE |tx|\| Dimension \| Question \|
M|ICE |tx|\|-----------\|----------\|
M|ICE |tx|\| **Impact** \| If this works, how much will it move the primary metric? \|
M|ICE |tx|\| **Confidence** \| How sure are we this will work? (Based on data, not gut.) \|
M|ICE |tx|\| **Ease** \| How fast and cheap can we ship and measure this? \|
M|ICE |tx|**ICE Score** = (Impact + Confidence + Ease) / 3
M|ICE |tx|Run highest-scoring experiments first. Re-score monthly as context changes.
M|Expe|Trac|
M|Expe|tx|\| Metric \| Target \|
M|Expe|tx|\|--------\|--------\|
M|Expe|tx|\| Experiments launched per month \| 4-8 for most teams \|
M|Expe|tx|\| Win rate \| 20-30% is common for mature programs (sustained higher rates may indicate conservative hypotheses) \|
M|Expe|tx|\| Average tst duration \| 2-4 weeks \|
M|Expe|tx|\| Backlog depth \| 20+ hypotheses queued \|
M|Expe|tx|\| Cumulative lift \| Compound gains from all winners \|
M|The |When|
M|The |tx|```
M|[Exp|**Da|[date]
M|[Exp|**Hy|[the hypothesis]
M|[Exp|**Sa|[n per variant]
M|[Exp|**Re|[winner/loser/inconclusive] — [primary metric] changed by [X%] (95% CI: [range], p=[value])
M|[Exp|**Gu|[any guardrail metrics and their outcomes]
M|[Exp|**Se|[notable differences by device, segment, or cohort]
M|[Exp|**Wh|[al]
M|[Exp|**Pa|[the reusable in — e.g., "sl proof near pricing CTAs increases plan selection"]
M|[Exp|**Ap|[other pages/flows where this pattern might work]
M|[Exp|**St|[implemented / parked / needs follow-up tst]
M|[Exp|tx|```
M|[Exp|tx|Over time, your playbook becomes a library of proven growth patterns specific to your pd and audience.
M|Expe|**We|rv running experiments for tc issues and guardrail metrics. Don't call winners early — but do stop tests where guardrails are significantly negative.
M|Expe|**Bi|Conclude done experiments. al results, up playbook, launch nx experiment from backlog.
M|Expe|**Mo|rv experiment velocity, win rate, cumulative lift. Replenish hypothesis backlog. Re-prioritize w/ ICE.
M|Expe|**Qu|Audit the playbook. Which patterns have been applied broadly? Which winning patterns haven't been scaled yet? What areas of the funnel are under-tested?
